---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import { Badge, Callout } from "pibarm-ds";
import PiSession from "../components/PiSession.jsx";
import MatrixDemo from "../components/Matrix.jsx";
---

<Base active="demo" title="pibarm — see it work">
  <div class="demo-head">
    <h1 class="demo-h1">See it work</h1>
    <p class="demo-lead">Two scripted simulations of pibarm in a real pi session. Both loop automatically — no install required to get the gist.</p>
  </div>

  <section class="demo-block">
    <div class="demo-cap">
      <span class="demo-cap-no">01</span>
      <h2 class="demo-cap-title">A planning session</h2>
      <span class="demo-cap-note">/plan → questions → /execute-plan worktree</span>
    </div>
    <div class="pib-demo-row">
      <PiSession client:visible />
      <div>
        <p class="demo-note">pi enters read-only plan mode, inspects the repo, and asks a clarifying question before proposing anything. Once you answer, it captures a plan and executes it in an isolated git worktree — your active checkout never moves.</p>
        <div style="display:flex;gap:8px;margin-top:14px;">
          <Badge tone="info" dot>read-only</Badge>
          <Badge tone="success" dot>worktree</Badge>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section class="demo-block">
    <div class="demo-cap">
      <span class="demo-cap-no">02</span>
      <h2 class="demo-cap-title">Matrix issue triage</h2>
      <span class="demo-cap-note">triage → plan → worktree → watch</span>
    </div>
    <p class="demo-note" style="max-width:70ch;margin-bottom:20px;">Using the repo's current open issues, scout maps scope while planner orders dependencies. Up to three agents share a horizontal row below the full-width parent; a fourth requires confirmation and moves to a new window. The parent loops through unblocked plans one worktree at a time and starts a watcher for each pull request's reviews and CI.</p>
    <MatrixDemo client:visible />
    <div style="margin-top:22px;">
      <Callout tone="tip" title="Why visible?">Parent-controlled panes mean you can watch and capture each agent's output live while the parent Pi remains usable — orchestration you can audit, not a black box.</Callout>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
